## Getting Started

### 1. Create an Account

Register at [https://softaware.net.za/register](https://softaware.net.za/register) or via API:

```bash
curl -X POST https://api.softaware.net.za/auth/register \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "email": "developer@example.com",
    "password": "SecurePass123!",
    "teamName": "My Company"
  }'
```

**Response:**
```json
{
  "accessToken": "eyJhbGci...",
  "user": {
    "id": "uuid-here",
    "email": "developer@example.com"
  },
  "team": {
    "id": "team-uuid",
    "name": "My Company"
  },
  "activationKey": "USER-XXXX"
}
```

### 2. Obtain API Credentials

After registration, generate an API key for server-side integrations:

```bash
curl -X POST https://api.softaware.net.za/api-keys \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "name": "Production API Key",
    "expiresInDays": 365
  }'
```

**Response:**
```json
{
  "id": "key-uuid",
  "name": "Production API Key",
  "key": "sk_live_abc123...xyz789",
  "isActive": true,
  "warning": "Save this key! It will not be shown again."
}
```

⚠️ **Store this key securely** — it provides full access to your account.

### 3. Make Your First Request

Test your credentials:

```bash
curl https://api.softaware.net.za/profile \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN"
```

Or using API key:

```bash
curl https://api.softaware.net.za/credits/balance \
  -H "X-API-Key: sk_live_abc123...xyz789"
```

